WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en-GB

00:00:05.600 --> 00:00:09.920
These are the chips powering
a transformational technology,

00:00:09.920 --> 00:00:16.480
reshaping how we live,
work, and communicate.

00:00:16.480 --> 00:00:20.840
They sit at the heart of a
new race between Washington

00:00:20.840 --> 00:00:22.160
and Beijing.

00:00:22.160 --> 00:00:26.000
The outcome will help determine
each superpower's status

00:00:26.000 --> 00:00:27.500
in a changing world.

00:00:27.500 --> 00:00:30.880
And right now, the most
advanced semiconductors

00:00:30.880 --> 00:00:33.840
are designed by US companies.

00:00:33.840 --> 00:00:37.150
They are also highly
sought after by China.

00:00:37.150 --> 00:00:40.160
The chips that go into
training and running models

00:00:40.160 --> 00:00:43.620
are the most complicated
things that humans make.

00:00:43.620 --> 00:00:46.990
These are maybe the most
valuable goods in the world.

00:00:46.990 --> 00:00:51.640
And US export controls are meant
to prevent their sale to China.

00:00:51.640 --> 00:00:56.160
But a thriving market for
smuggled silicon has emerged.

00:00:56.160 --> 00:00:58.220
The stakes are enormous.

00:00:58.220 --> 00:01:02.300
China cares, both from a
technology point of view,

00:01:02.300 --> 00:01:05.519
a business point of view, and
a political point of view.

00:01:05.519 --> 00:01:09.040
We're going to show you how
this illegal trade works.

00:01:09.040 --> 00:01:10.760
This guy is claiming
that he's just

00:01:10.760 --> 00:01:15.280
taken stock of a big
load of H200's that's

00:01:15.280 --> 00:01:16.920
come through Hong
Kong and is going

00:01:16.920 --> 00:01:19.720
to be delivered to Shenzhen.

00:01:19.720 --> 00:01:22.960
We will also reveal
how the controls are

00:01:22.960 --> 00:01:25.480
tearing Chinese
and US technology

00:01:25.480 --> 00:01:31.200
companies apart and forcing
Chinese chip makers to innovate.

00:01:31.200 --> 00:01:35.680
It has also opened a new sphere
of competition between the two

00:01:35.680 --> 00:01:37.360
superpowers.

00:01:37.360 --> 00:01:42.040
But first, let's explain
what export controls are

00:01:42.040 --> 00:01:44.540
and why they're being
used by Washington.

00:01:53.000 --> 00:01:57.400
Why is China so desperate to
acquire US designated chips?

00:01:57.400 --> 00:01:59.350
The reason is obvious.

00:01:59.350 --> 00:02:02.590
AI is truly
transformative technology

00:02:02.590 --> 00:02:06.690
and it's already changing how we
fight wars, run our government,

00:02:06.690 --> 00:02:08.830
and operate companies.

00:02:08.830 --> 00:02:10.470
It's essential for
the United States

00:02:10.470 --> 00:02:14.550
to maintain a decisive
lead in the AI race.

00:02:14.550 --> 00:02:19.430
In 2022, the US government
introduced blanket bans

00:02:19.430 --> 00:02:22.570
on the sale of the most
advanced chips to China.

00:02:22.570 --> 00:02:24.770
These chips were
invented in America.

00:02:24.770 --> 00:02:25.770
Let's get that straight.

00:02:25.770 --> 00:02:27.370
They were invented in America.

00:02:28.830 --> 00:02:32.370
And we used to make 40%
of the world's chips.

00:02:36.510 --> 00:02:40.390
Export controls were born in the
aftermath of the Second world

00:02:40.390 --> 00:02:45.390
war, when the world was divided
along ideological lines.

00:02:45.390 --> 00:02:48.270
The US and its
allies on one side,

00:02:48.270 --> 00:02:51.190
the Soviet Union on the other.

00:02:51.190 --> 00:02:55.850
Both sides were locked in a cold
war and a nuclear arms race.

00:02:59.150 --> 00:03:02.390
Washington knew that
technological supremacy would

00:03:02.390 --> 00:03:04.670
ensure military dominance.

00:03:04.670 --> 00:03:08.990
So in 1949, it created
rules to stop Moscow

00:03:08.990 --> 00:03:12.090
from obtaining critical
western technology.

00:03:15.150 --> 00:03:19.590
But the fall of the Berlin Wall
and the dawn of the 21st century

00:03:19.590 --> 00:03:24.190
created a new strategic rivalry,
this time between the US

00:03:24.190 --> 00:03:26.630
and a rising China.

00:03:26.630 --> 00:03:31.270
Many in Washington see Beijing
as a threat to the US-led world

00:03:31.270 --> 00:03:34.070
order, and China's
AI development

00:03:34.070 --> 00:03:36.350
as something that
must be curtailed.

00:03:36.350 --> 00:03:39.430
It has turned to this
cold war era rule book

00:03:39.430 --> 00:03:41.770
to stop its new rival.

00:03:45.590 --> 00:03:50.430
Kevin Kurland spent 28 years
at the Department of Commerce.

00:03:50.430 --> 00:03:54.030
Most advanced chips,
and certainly AI chips

00:03:54.030 --> 00:03:56.970
that are designed
by US companies

00:03:56.970 --> 00:04:00.710
and many western companies, are
virtually all fabbed or produced

00:04:00.710 --> 00:04:04.550
in Taiwan, usually at TSMC.

00:04:04.550 --> 00:04:08.150
And then those products
either get packaged in Taiwan

00:04:08.150 --> 00:04:09.930
or in third countries.

00:04:09.930 --> 00:04:12.270
And then from the
packagers they're

00:04:12.270 --> 00:04:18.010
directed then to either send
the items back to the designer,

00:04:18.010 --> 00:04:20.950
or many times they're
just directly sent

00:04:20.950 --> 00:04:25.530
to an integrator, if you
will, or a distribution chain.

00:04:25.530 --> 00:04:29.950
And so in order to harden
these supply chains,

00:04:29.950 --> 00:04:33.430
you really need to have an
export compliance programme that

00:04:33.430 --> 00:04:37.810
not only addresses the
activities that are happening,

00:04:37.810 --> 00:04:40.910
for example, in
the United States,

00:04:40.910 --> 00:04:45.290
but their distribution networks
and who their customers are.

00:04:48.690 --> 00:04:51.590
In this tech war between
China and the US,

00:04:51.590 --> 00:04:54.940
Taiwan plays a critical role.

00:04:54.940 --> 00:04:57.700
The island has emerged
as an essential node

00:04:57.700 --> 00:05:00.660
in the global
semiconductor supply chain.

00:05:00.660 --> 00:05:04.060
That Beijing wants to
reunify with Taiwan has only

00:05:04.060 --> 00:05:09.820
added to the geopolitical
significance of this story.

00:05:09.820 --> 00:05:13.700
I've witnessed Taiwan's
growth into an AI powerhouse,

00:05:13.700 --> 00:05:17.220
first as a student and
later as a reporter.

00:05:17.220 --> 00:05:20.940
I've returned to Taipei to
attend Computex, the world's

00:05:20.940 --> 00:05:24.060
most important chip conference.

00:05:24.060 --> 00:05:28.460
What is on display here today
is the most leading edge

00:05:28.460 --> 00:05:32.860
AI products, which are not
allowed for export in China.

00:05:32.860 --> 00:05:36.900
These AI chips have become more
and more powerful, more and more

00:05:36.900 --> 00:05:40.240
capable of training bigger
and more powerful AI models,

00:05:40.240 --> 00:05:43.820
and the American government
has stopped Chinese companies

00:05:43.820 --> 00:05:47.340
from getting their
hands on these chips.

00:05:47.340 --> 00:05:51.020
So this is one of the racks that
go into the large data centre

00:05:51.020 --> 00:05:51.660
product.

00:05:51.660 --> 00:05:54.700
It's full of Nvidia
GPUs that are

00:05:54.700 --> 00:05:58.660
essential for model training
and inference, i.e.,

00:05:58.660 --> 00:06:01.500
the process of
running AI models.

00:06:01.500 --> 00:06:03.820
And these chips are
among the series

00:06:03.820 --> 00:06:07.980
that are restricted
for shipment to China.

00:06:07.980 --> 00:06:11.260
Chris McGuire has advised
both the Biden and Trump

00:06:11.260 --> 00:06:15.100
administrations on China
and emerging technologies.

00:06:15.100 --> 00:06:17.580
Computing power is the
core input into AI.

00:06:17.580 --> 00:06:20.220
It is the reason that training
and developing these models

00:06:20.220 --> 00:06:23.500
is the most expensive thing
that humans are doing right now.

00:06:23.500 --> 00:06:25.900
Nvidia is just the
example, frequently,

00:06:25.900 --> 00:06:27.680
because they are so significant.

00:06:27.680 --> 00:06:31.270
They are somewhere between 80%
to 90% of the AI chip market.

00:06:31.270 --> 00:06:33.020
The reason for that
is that their products

00:06:33.020 --> 00:06:34.320
are extremely good.

00:06:34.320 --> 00:06:35.880
They're very, very good chips.

00:06:35.880 --> 00:06:37.740
They're very, very powerful.

00:06:37.740 --> 00:06:41.220
Nvidia has very, very robust
supply chains where they can

00:06:41.220 --> 00:06:44.740
ensure, they can really maximise
their output and ensure delivery

00:06:44.740 --> 00:06:46.520
on time to customers
as well as they can,

00:06:46.520 --> 00:06:49.300
given the kind of supply
constraints that they have.

00:06:49.300 --> 00:06:51.620
The world's most
valuable company

00:06:51.620 --> 00:06:55.260
is now at the heart
of geopolitics.

00:06:55.260 --> 00:06:57.760
The United States is
ahead in the AI race,

00:06:57.760 --> 00:06:59.480
and we have to stay
ahead in the AI race.

00:06:59.480 --> 00:07:01.720
So we've taken China
out of our forecast.

00:07:01.720 --> 00:07:04.240
We're currently
shipping zero dollars.

00:07:04.240 --> 00:07:07.045
Our market share has
gone from 95% to 0.

00:07:07.045 --> 00:07:08.420
We're currently
assuming China is

00:07:08.420 --> 00:07:10.760
going to be 0% of our business.

00:07:10.760 --> 00:07:15.100
But winning the AI race has
become a priority for Beijing.

00:07:15.100 --> 00:07:18.100
President Xi Jinping is
marshalling both the state

00:07:18.100 --> 00:07:22.140
and private sectors to
catch up with the US.

00:07:22.140 --> 00:07:23.820
The Chinese Ministry
of State Security

00:07:23.820 --> 00:07:27.340
has recently said that
circumventing the US technology

00:07:27.340 --> 00:07:29.720
blockade is one of
its top priorities.

00:07:29.720 --> 00:07:33.060
It's certain that there are
diversion campaigns that

00:07:33.060 --> 00:07:37.580
are being facilitated by the
Chinese intelligence services

00:07:37.580 --> 00:07:39.920
in order to support their
technology companies.

00:07:39.920 --> 00:07:41.200
This also is not surprising.

00:07:41.200 --> 00:07:43.780
This is an asset that they
absolutely need to stay

00:07:43.780 --> 00:07:45.960
competitive, that they
cannot make themselves.

00:07:45.960 --> 00:07:48.890
And the only way that they can
actually remain competitive

00:07:48.890 --> 00:07:52.330
is by either convincing the
United States to give it

00:07:52.330 --> 00:07:55.407
to them, smuggling it,
or exploiting loopholes

00:07:55.407 --> 00:07:57.490
in the export controls
that allow them to continue

00:07:57.490 --> 00:07:58.910
to have access to them.

00:07:58.910 --> 00:08:01.770
Without those things, there
would be a very significant drop

00:08:01.770 --> 00:08:04.170
off for Chinese AI capabilities,
and I think the Chinese

00:08:04.170 --> 00:08:06.890
government recognises that and
is pulling out all the stops

00:08:06.890 --> 00:08:08.890
in order to prevent
that from happening.

00:08:08.890 --> 00:08:12.370
Shares of Super Micro
Computer losing about a third

00:08:12.370 --> 00:08:13.350
of their value.

00:08:13.350 --> 00:08:17.030
It's because of an
international smuggling scandal.

00:08:17.030 --> 00:08:20.490
In March this year, the
US Department of Justice

00:08:20.490 --> 00:08:24.370
targeted employees at
Supermicro, a Taiwanese company

00:08:24.370 --> 00:08:26.130
and Nvidia partner.

00:08:26.130 --> 00:08:31.690
They stand accused of smuggling
$2.5bn worth of Nvidia chips

00:08:31.690 --> 00:08:34.330
and servers into China.

00:08:34.330 --> 00:08:36.289
The US alleges that
a front company

00:08:36.289 --> 00:08:38.530
was used to divert the chips.

00:08:38.530 --> 00:08:41.929
Supermicro was not named as
a defendant in the indictment

00:08:41.929 --> 00:08:47.170
and has denied any wrongdoing,
as have the named defendants.

00:08:47.170 --> 00:08:49.530
Still, analysts
say that the case

00:08:49.530 --> 00:08:53.770
highlights historic failings
of the export control regime.

00:08:53.770 --> 00:08:57.610
The smuggling really ranges from
mum and pop smuggling operations

00:08:57.610 --> 00:09:02.130
to very large, systematic
criminal organisations.

00:09:02.130 --> 00:09:05.450
Nvidia makes somewhere between
5mn and 10mn of these chips per

00:09:05.450 --> 00:09:06.030
year.

00:09:06.030 --> 00:09:08.230
If there's three or four
that go out in a backpack,

00:09:08.230 --> 00:09:09.710
obviously you want to stop that.

00:09:09.710 --> 00:09:13.370
But if you have organisations
that are funnelling tens

00:09:13.370 --> 00:09:16.510
of thousands of chips,
that's a significant problem.

00:09:16.510 --> 00:09:19.530
And I think that we've seen
organisations are committed

00:09:19.530 --> 00:09:23.430
to that because this is an
extremely valuable industry.

00:09:29.610 --> 00:09:33.570
So I've been reporting
on the various tactics

00:09:33.570 --> 00:09:38.730
Chinese companies have used to
get their hands on American AI

00:09:38.730 --> 00:09:41.330
chips for about four years now.

00:09:41.330 --> 00:09:45.450
It's been an evolving
story, and these companies

00:09:45.450 --> 00:09:48.730
have been using ever
more creative loopholes,

00:09:48.730 --> 00:09:52.890
some legal, some illegal.

00:09:52.890 --> 00:09:55.530
Last year we published
an investigation

00:09:55.530 --> 00:10:00.930
that provided a snapshot into
how these large-scale chip

00:10:00.930 --> 00:10:03.270
smuggling operations work.

00:10:03.270 --> 00:10:08.490
We found a paper trail of
contracts and had discussions

00:10:08.490 --> 00:10:12.490
with middlemen, and found
evidence of at least $1bn

00:10:12.490 --> 00:10:16.250
of Nvidia GPUs being
brought into China.

00:10:16.250 --> 00:10:20.930
The estimated number of chips
sold here on the black market

00:10:20.930 --> 00:10:22.790
is far higher than that.

00:10:22.790 --> 00:10:25.450
But really, this story
provided an insight

00:10:25.450 --> 00:10:29.670
into how the larger-scale
operation works.

00:10:32.210 --> 00:10:36.090
So I'm on Xiaohongshu here,
which is a Chinese social media

00:10:36.090 --> 00:10:37.110
platform.

00:10:37.110 --> 00:10:41.290
And if you type in
Nvidia or AMD you'll

00:10:41.290 --> 00:10:43.480
come up with a lot of
these kinds of posts

00:10:43.480 --> 00:10:47.600
by middlemen selling
these smuggled chips.

00:10:47.600 --> 00:10:50.260
Here, we have H200s.

00:10:50.260 --> 00:10:52.820
There's also someone
selling B300s,

00:10:52.820 --> 00:10:56.080
which is a more
advanced Nvidia series.

00:10:56.080 --> 00:10:58.660
And if you go onto
their profiles,

00:10:58.660 --> 00:11:03.920
these guys are very clearly
advertising their sales.

00:11:03.920 --> 00:11:05.640
This guy is claiming
that he's just

00:11:05.640 --> 00:11:10.200
taken stock of a big
load of H200s that's

00:11:10.200 --> 00:11:11.920
come through Hong
Kong and is going

00:11:11.920 --> 00:11:13.820
to be delivered to Shenzhen.

00:11:16.920 --> 00:11:20.400
Shenzhen is important
for the chip smuggling

00:11:20.400 --> 00:11:24.240
story for a variety of different
reasons, the first of which

00:11:24.240 --> 00:11:26.380
is it's a port city.

00:11:26.380 --> 00:11:28.640
It's close to Hong
Kong, which is

00:11:28.640 --> 00:11:31.720
a thoroughfare for a lot
of these smuggled chips.

00:11:31.720 --> 00:11:35.340
It is also a place where
there's a lot of AI hardware.

00:11:35.340 --> 00:11:37.820
So server builders,
rack builders.

00:11:37.820 --> 00:11:39.760
It's somewhere where
the chips are just

00:11:39.760 --> 00:11:43.160
being sold and repackaged
to the rest of China.

00:11:43.160 --> 00:11:46.620
There are a lot of tech
salesmen based in Shenzhen.

00:11:46.620 --> 00:11:48.420
It's a hardware hub in China.

00:11:48.420 --> 00:11:50.280
And so if you've
got requirements

00:11:50.280 --> 00:11:53.408
for new computers, new servers,
you go down to Shenzhen.

00:11:53.408 --> 00:11:55.200
You speak to these
middlemen, and they will

00:11:55.200 --> 00:11:58.600
create you a custom solution.

00:11:58.600 --> 00:12:02.840
We are here at Huatung Bay in
Shenzhen, a famous electronics

00:12:02.840 --> 00:12:03.500
market.

00:12:03.500 --> 00:12:06.680
You can find any
electronics component here,

00:12:06.680 --> 00:12:10.023
including lots of people
selling second-hand chips.

00:12:10.023 --> 00:12:12.440
So we're going to go and see
if we can find anyone selling

00:12:12.440 --> 00:12:15.200
Nvidia GPUs in here today.

00:12:15.200 --> 00:12:18.280
The market is a labyrinth
of retailers selling

00:12:18.280 --> 00:12:20.560
all kinds of
consumer electronics

00:12:20.560 --> 00:12:22.880
and the components
that go into them.

00:12:22.880 --> 00:12:25.880
I'm here to talk
with a chip reseller.

00:12:25.880 --> 00:12:28.640
He's agreed to be interviewed,
but not on camera,

00:12:28.640 --> 00:12:30.900
given the sensitivity
of the topic.

00:13:08.070 --> 00:13:12.070
Until recently, it was also
possible to buy smuggled AI

00:13:12.070 --> 00:13:15.030
chips from Nvidia and AMD.

00:13:15.030 --> 00:13:17.230
But in recent months
it's become incredibly

00:13:17.230 --> 00:13:21.390
difficult to get access to these
because the Chinese authorities

00:13:21.390 --> 00:13:24.190
have restricted
imports of these chips

00:13:24.190 --> 00:13:26.870
in order to support
local competitors.

00:13:26.870 --> 00:13:28.830
That means that
the prices of these

00:13:28.830 --> 00:13:30.710
have gone absolutely crazy.

00:13:30.710 --> 00:13:33.910
We've spoken to a number of
sellers in this building,

00:13:33.910 --> 00:13:36.890
and they said that prices
have gone absolutely crazy,

00:13:36.890 --> 00:13:40.190
exacerbated also by the
memory chip shortage.

00:13:40.190 --> 00:13:46.390
But for example, one seller
said that one B300 machine, that

00:13:46.390 --> 00:13:49.350
is one of the leading
server machines,

00:13:49.350 --> 00:13:53.070
has almost doubled in
price in recent months.

00:13:53.070 --> 00:13:55.910
Chinese companies are
also exploiting loopholes

00:13:55.910 --> 00:14:00.230
in the US export controls by
remotely accessing restricted

00:14:00.230 --> 00:14:02.130
chips.

00:14:02.130 --> 00:14:04.950
Right now, the
administration has not

00:14:04.950 --> 00:14:11.110
articulated a coherent strategy
for controlling advanced compute

00:14:11.110 --> 00:14:12.450
and AI chips.

00:14:12.450 --> 00:14:16.750
The most advanced Nvidia chips,
say a Blackwell that is located

00:14:16.750 --> 00:14:20.990
in a data centre in Malaysia,
there is no restriction on any

00:14:20.990 --> 00:14:25.250
Chinese company from accessing
the compute power on that item.

00:14:25.250 --> 00:14:27.210
So there's an
inconsistency there.

00:14:27.210 --> 00:14:32.670
There's also a loophole in the
current regulations that do not

00:14:32.670 --> 00:14:37.390
restrict a Chinese front
company in a third country,

00:14:37.390 --> 00:14:40.870
or a Chinese-owned data
centre in a third country,

00:14:40.870 --> 00:14:45.070
from buying the same chips or
servers that are restricted

00:14:45.070 --> 00:14:47.050
for sale directly to China.

00:14:52.030 --> 00:14:55.310
So on the one hand, you
have the Chinese AI labs

00:14:55.310 --> 00:14:57.370
who want to build
the best models,

00:14:57.370 --> 00:15:00.150
and it just so happens that
building the best model

00:15:00.150 --> 00:15:03.390
means access to Nvidia GPUs.

00:15:03.390 --> 00:15:05.910
But on the other hand, you also
have Chinese tech companies

00:15:05.910 --> 00:15:09.990
that are trying to support the
growth of domestic AI chips,

00:15:09.990 --> 00:15:11.790
like Huawei and Capricorn.

00:15:11.790 --> 00:15:13.910
And their argument
is that we should

00:15:13.910 --> 00:15:17.970
be supporting the growth
of these domestic chips.

00:15:17.970 --> 00:15:22.390
And if that means relinquishing
some progress or lead on AI

00:15:22.390 --> 00:15:24.210
in the short term, that's OK.

00:15:24.210 --> 00:15:28.150
We should be doing it for the
long-term goal of Chinese AI

00:15:28.150 --> 00:15:29.290
independence.

00:16:03.700 --> 00:16:08.780
I don't buy that export
controls are driving China

00:16:08.780 --> 00:16:10.160
to self-sufficiency.

00:16:10.160 --> 00:16:12.900
They had already put
out a policy to do that.

00:16:12.900 --> 00:16:15.140
To me, again,
export controls are

00:16:15.140 --> 00:16:20.020
meant to maintain US leadership
by delaying their ability

00:16:20.020 --> 00:16:25.220
to achieve the same goals,
or levels of innovation, that

00:16:25.220 --> 00:16:29.160
allow the United States to
continue to be a leader,

00:16:29.160 --> 00:16:32.800
both from an economic and a
national security perspective.

00:16:32.800 --> 00:16:35.980
The question is,
ultimately, will China

00:16:35.980 --> 00:16:39.700
be able to reach a level
where Huawei or one

00:16:39.700 --> 00:16:41.780
of the other
Chinese AI companies

00:16:41.780 --> 00:16:45.920
is equally or even better
than the American companies?

00:16:45.920 --> 00:16:48.760
And I think that's still
a massive open question.

00:16:48.760 --> 00:16:53.100
It looks like a no for now, but
China has proven time and time

00:16:53.100 --> 00:16:55.220
again that it's very
capable of building

00:16:55.220 --> 00:16:56.720
cutting-edge technology.

00:16:59.785 --> 00:17:03.440
Right now, the US leads by
about eight months in AI.

00:17:03.440 --> 00:17:05.720
That's per the latest
US government estimate.

00:17:05.720 --> 00:17:08.099
It also means that AI is
doubling in capability

00:17:08.099 --> 00:17:09.520
about every four months.

00:17:09.520 --> 00:17:13.720
So an 8-month lead means about
a 4x capability difference.

00:17:13.720 --> 00:17:16.460
That's significant, but
it's also not so significant

00:17:16.460 --> 00:17:19.140
that I think the Chinese say,
OK, well we're down and out.

00:17:19.140 --> 00:17:19.880
Right?

00:17:19.880 --> 00:17:22.588
They're looking at this like, we
have an opportunity to catch up.

00:17:22.588 --> 00:17:25.400
We're behind, but we think
we can close the gap.

00:17:25.400 --> 00:17:27.540
We certainly have
become obsessed

00:17:27.540 --> 00:17:31.700
with this idea of a time lag
between the US and China.

00:17:31.700 --> 00:17:35.840
To me, I don't think it matters
a huge amount right now.

00:17:35.840 --> 00:17:39.580
What certainly does
matter is whether or not

00:17:39.580 --> 00:17:43.700
the US is the first to
build this fated future

00:17:43.700 --> 00:17:46.040
of super general intelligence.

00:17:46.040 --> 00:17:48.800
And if and when we
get to that stage,

00:17:48.800 --> 00:17:50.620
it certainly looks
like America is

00:17:50.620 --> 00:17:52.520
going to be the
first to get there,

00:17:52.520 --> 00:17:55.750
given the trajectory of the
model development at the moment.

00:17:55.750 --> 00:17:58.380
The United States just needs
to recognise that the US

00:17:58.380 --> 00:18:02.340
and Chinese AI ecosystems
are fundamentally diverging.

00:18:02.340 --> 00:18:04.540
That is exactly how it
was in the cold war.

00:18:04.540 --> 00:18:08.100
The US and Soviet nuclear
programmes in no way helped each

00:18:08.100 --> 00:18:08.600
other.

00:18:08.600 --> 00:18:11.700
They were completely separate,
and that is undoubtedly

00:18:11.700 --> 00:18:14.240
in the national security
interests of the United States.

00:18:14.240 --> 00:18:17.500
That also did not preclude
co-operation between the United

00:18:17.500 --> 00:18:20.420
States and the Soviet Union
on certain discrete areas

00:18:20.420 --> 00:18:22.160
where we had shared interests.

00:18:22.160 --> 00:18:25.220
And I think in AI we probably
need to think about co-operation

00:18:25.220 --> 00:18:27.280
with China more in that sense.

00:18:31.690 --> 00:18:36.370
For now, the US dominance
in AI hardware is clear.

00:18:36.370 --> 00:18:39.610
There are several chokeholds
that Chinese companies have not

00:18:39.610 --> 00:18:41.090
yet broken.

00:18:41.090 --> 00:18:43.570
It will take time
and a lot of money

00:18:43.570 --> 00:18:47.050
to build a rival ecosystem
to the one Nvidia

00:18:47.050 --> 00:18:49.170
and its partners
have established.

00:18:49.170 --> 00:18:51.450
But what we have
seen time and time

00:18:51.450 --> 00:18:55.250
again is China build
technology that the world said

00:18:55.250 --> 00:18:57.730
was outside of its grasp.

00:18:57.730 --> 00:19:00.330
We know that Beijing
is pouring investment

00:19:00.330 --> 00:19:04.650
into becoming a
self-sufficient AI state.

00:19:04.650 --> 00:19:06.290
Can it succeed?

00:19:06.290 --> 00:19:10.920
This is a story that will
define the world's future.

